and whether that might prompt many people to shut down their E*Trade accoun=
ts in solidarity, the people said.He=E2=80=99s not=C2=A0really=C2=A0just on=
e retail trader; he=E2=80=99s the voice of a movement, and if E*Trade shut =
him down they might lose a lot of customers. So they need a really good rea=
son to act.I suspect that's true of the SEC, too, by the way. Gill=E2=80=99=
s posting and trading are not=C2=A0just ambiguous; they are also extremely =
popular and politically charged. If the SEC tries to shut him down, there a=
re going to be angry letters and tweets and congressional hearings. If it=
=E2=80=99s going to stop this, the SEC had better be sure that it's right.
